title: IPackAndGo.GetDocumentSaveToNames
description: Gets the paths and filenames to which to save the model's documents for Pack and Go set by IPackAndGo::SetDocumentSaveToNames.
signature:
System.Boolean GetDocumentSaveToNames( 
   out System.Object
PathNameList
,
   out System.Object
DocumentStatusList
)

parameters.name: PathNameList
parameters.description: Array of strings containing the path and filenames to which to save the model's documents (see Remarks )

parameters.name: DocumentStatusList
parameters.description: Array containing the types of documents as defined in swPackAndGoDocumentStatus_e

returns: True if the paths and filenames of the model's documents are returned, false if not
remarks:
The order and number of documents must match the order of the array returned by
IPackAndGo::GetDocumentNames
. If a
prefix
or
suffix
is set, then the filenames include it. You can set both a prefix and suffix for the filenames.
